This paper is about reinforcement learning for dialogue policy optimization, which is a common topic in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of multi-objective reinforcement learning also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The application of the proposed method to six domains suggests a potential interest in speech and dialogue processing (cs.SD). Finally, the goal of improving dialogue success and length suggests a potential interest in human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
